<div class="profile edit">
	{{> card }}
	
	<div class="explanation">
		<h2>Here's What's Up</h2>
		<p>You've got an indicator! It will monitor your inbox and your behavior to determine what a "normal inbox" is <em>for you</em>. When your inbox is "normal" it will appear yellow, when it's good: green, and overfull: red. Inbox zero will always be green, no matter your habits. Right now it's got some "stupid" defaults, as time goes on it will adapt to you.</p>
		<h2>Using the Indicator</h2>
		<p>
			To use the indicator, simply select &amp; copy the following indicator. Paste it into your <a href="https://mail.google.com/mail/#settings/general">signature</a> or anywhere else you might like.
		</p>

		<div id="indicator-signature">
			<a href="http://indicator.email/user/{{ user.userHash }}/" title="{{ user.email }}" style="border: 0;">
				<img width="99" height="20" src="https://indicator-email.herokuapp.com/user/{{ user.userHash }}/indicator.png" alt="Inbox Status â€¢">
			</a>
		</div>

		<div class="copy button has-icon" id="copy-indicator-signature" data-clipboard-target="indicator-signature">
			<div class="icon">
				<object class="download" data="/assets/img/clipboard-download.svg" type="image/svg+xml"></object>
				<object class="checked" data="/assets/img/clipboard-checked.svg" type="image/svg+xml"></object>
			</div>
			<div class="text">Copy</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>